# Cursor Rules — Synkra AIOS Design System

## Design System Foundation

### Color System
- Use design tokens from `src/tokens/index.ts`
- Prefix colors: `primary-`, `secondary-`, `success-`, `warning-`, `error-`, `neutral-`
- Dark mode: Use `[data-theme="dark"]` or Tailwind's `dark:` prefix

### Component Structure (Atomic Design)
- **Atoms:** `src/components/ui/` — Button, Input, Badge, Card, etc
- **Molecules:** `src/components/composite/` — FormField, Alert, etc
- **Organisms:** `src/components/layout/` — Header, Sidebar, Footer, etc

### Styling Rules
- ✅ **DO:** Use Tailwind classes from `tailwind.config.ts`
- ✅ **DO:** Import utility function `cn()` from `src/lib/utils.ts`
- ✅ **DO:** Use semantic color names: `text-primary`, `bg-surface-hover`
- ✅ **DO:** Leverage component tokens: `button`, `input`, `card`, `badge`
- ❌ **DON'T:** Hardcode colors (use token values instead)
- ❌ **DON'T:** Use `className` strings without `cn()` for conditional classes
- ❌ **DON'T:** Create CSS modules or inline styles (token-driven approach)

### Import Patterns
```typescript
// ✅ Good
import { cn } from '@/lib/utils';
import { colors, spacing, typography } from '@/tokens';

// ❌ Avoid
import styles from './component.module.css'; // No CSS modules
<div style={{ color: 'red' }} /> // No inline styles
```

### Dark Mode Implementation
```typescript
// ✅ Use this approach
export function MyComponent() {
  return (
    <div className="bg-neutral-0 dark:bg-neutral-900 text-neutral-900 dark:text-neutral-0">
      Content
    </div>
  );
}

// Helper functions available
import { isDarkMode, toggleDarkMode, setDarkMode } from '@/lib/utils';
```

### Component Export Pattern
```typescript
// All components export props interface and component
export interface MyComponentProps {
  variant?: 'primary' | 'secondary';
  size?: 'sm' | 'md' | 'lg';
  className?: string;
}

export function MyComponent({ variant = 'primary', ...props }: MyComponentProps) {
  return <div className={cn('base-classes', `variant-${variant}`, props.className)} />;
}
```

### Testing
- Location: `src/__tests__/` for shared utilities
- Pattern: `ComponentName.test.tsx`
- Use React Testing Library + jest-axe for a11y
- Example: `src/components/ui/Button.test.tsx`

### Documentation
- Create `.stories.tsx` files for each component
- Pattern: `src/components/ui/Button.stories.tsx`
- Use Storybook controls for prop variations
- Document accessibility requirements

## TypeScript Configuration

- Strict mode enabled
- Path alias: `@/*` maps to `src/*`
- Target: ES2022
- Module: ESNext

## Tailwind CSS v4

- Extended colors from design tokens
- Spacing system: 4px base unit
- Border radius standardized
- Shadow system pre-configured
- Dark mode: `[data-theme="dark"]` attribute

## File Naming Conventions

- **Components:** PascalCase (Button.tsx, FormField.tsx)
- **Utilities:** camelCase (utils.ts, hooks.ts)
- **Types:** filename.types.ts or inline interface
- **Tests:** Component.test.tsx or Component.spec.tsx
- **Stories:** Component.stories.tsx

## Accessibility Standards

- Target: WCAG AA minimum
- Focus visible: `outline-2 outline-offset-2 outline-primary-500`
- Dark mode contrast: Verify with jest-axe
- Semantic HTML: Use proper headings, labels, buttons
- ARIA labels: Only when necessary (prefer semantic HTML)

## Performance Guidelines

- Use `cn()` for conditional classes (prevents Tailwind purging issues)
- Lazy load components with React.lazy if >50KB
- Memoize expensive computations with useMemo
- Use useCallback for event handlers in lists

## Git Commit Messages

- Format: `type(scope): description [Story ID]`
- Types: feat, fix, docs, style, refactor, test, chore
- Example: `feat(button): add ghost variant [Story 2.1]`

## Storybook Standards

- Every component must have `.stories.tsx` file
- Include: default, variants, states, dark mode
- Use Controls addon for prop exploration
- Document component purpose and usage

## Environment Variables

- Location: `.env.local` (git-ignored)
- Never commit secrets
- Use `process.env.NEXT_PUBLIC_*` for client-side

## Quick Commands

```bash
npm run storybook          # Start Storybook
npm test                   # Run tests
npm run lint               # Lint code
npm run typecheck          # Type checking
npm run build              # Production build

# Design System agents
*build button              # Create new component
*compose form-field        # Combine atoms into molecule
*document                  # Generate Storybook docs
*a11y-check                # Accessibility audit
```

